{"apiname": "zip_file_replace", "link": "https://libzip.org/documentation/zip_file_replace.html", "lib": "libzip", "sentence": "  zip_file_add, zip_file_replace    -  add file to zip archive or replace file in zip archive ", "doc": "  The function zip_file_add() adds a file to a zip   archive, while zip_file_replace() replaces an existing   file in a zip archive. The argument archive specifies   the zip archive to which the file should be added. name   is the file's name in the zip archive (for   zip_file_add()), while index   specifies which file should be replaced (for   zip_file_replace()). The flags   argument can be any combination of ZIP_FL_OVERWRITE   with one of ZIP_FL_ENC_*:  ZIP_FL_OVERWRITE Overwrite any existing file of the same name. For       zip_file_add only. ZIP_FL_ENC_GUESS Guess encoding of name (default). (Only CP-437 and       UTF-8 are recognized.) ZIP_FL_ENC_UTF_8 Interpret name as UTF-8. ZIP_FL_ENC_CP437 Interpret name as code page 437 (CP-437).  The data is obtained from the source argument, see   zip_source(3). NOTE:     zip_source_free(3) should not     be called on a source after it was used successfully     in a zip_file_add or     zip_file_replace call. ", "sentence_type": "", "first_sentence": 0}
