{"apiname": "zip_source_win32a", "link": "https://libzip.org/documentation/zip_source_win32a.html", "lib": "libzip", "sentence": "  zip_source_win32a,   zip_source_win32a_create  -  create data source from a Windows ANSI file name ", "doc": "  The functions zip_source_win32a() and   zip_source_win32a_create() create a zip source on   Windows using a Windows ANSI name. They open fname and   read len bytes from offset start   from it. If len is 0 or -1, the whole file (starting   from start) is used. If the file supports seek, the source can be used to open a zip     archive from. The file is opened and read when the data from the source is used,     usually by zip_close() or     zip_open_from_source(). ", "sentence_type": "", "first_sentence": 0}
