{"apiname": "zip_source_zip", "link": "https://libzip.org/documentation/zip_source_zip.html", "lib": "libzip", "sentence": "  zip_source_zip,   zip_source_zip_create  -  create data source from zip file ", "doc": "  The functions zip_source_zip() and   zip_source_zip_create() create a zip source from a   file in a zip archive. The srcarchive argument is the   (open) zip archive containing the source zip file at index   srcidx. len bytes from offset   start will be used in the zip_source. If   len is 0 or -1, the rest of the file, starting from   start, is used. If start is zero   and len is -1, the whole file will be copied without   decompressing it. Supported flags are:  ZIP_FL_UNCHANGED Try to get the original data without any changes that may have been made       to srcarchive after opening it. ZIP_FL_RECOMPRESS When adding the data from srcarchive, re-compress it       using the current settings instead of copying the compressed data.  ", "sentence_type": "", "first_sentence": 0}
